  <description type="morphology">Plants robust, in loose tufts, mostly green to yellow, shiny.  Stems 1–2(–4) cm.  Leaves mostly falcate-secund, lanceolate, gradually subulate, 2–4.5 mm, margins distally 1 or 2-stratose; costa 50–60 µm wide at base; distal laminal cells mostly elongate (2–5:1), porose, 7–9 µm wide, smooth or weakly mammillose-roughened; basal laminal cells elongate, porose, alar cells strongly inflated and differentiated.  Perichaetial leaves similar to the cauline.  Perigonia sessile, located just below perichaetia.  Capsule distinctly ribbed when dry, urn 1.3–2 mm.  Spores 14–20 µm.</description>
  <description type="morphology">Soil over rock;</description>
